cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DM 

This paper deals with the complexity of SAT problems and the representation of boolean constraints, which are topics that fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper's focus on XOR-constraints may also suggest a connection to cryptography (cs.CR). However, given the emphasis on complexity and representation, the first five categories are more likely to be relevant.
